cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with capacity regions and inner bounds on the capacity region for uplink and downlink communications in cloud radio access networks. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper models cloud radio access networks as two-hop K-user L-relay networks and discusses the fronthaul links connecting the small base-stations to the central processor. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper discusses the capacity regions and scaling laws of cloud radio access networks, which are relevant to communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents simplified versions of network compress-forward and distributed decode-forward to establish inner bounds on the capacity region, which are related to system and control. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses distributed decode-forward, which is a distributed computing technique, and also presents simulation results for the capacity scaling law in the large network size limit.
